I agree dice are too advanced and finicky a topic to work with now, but I've
made my position on attributes clear.

>This net group can create a GREAT game.  It can create a GREAT game that
>has a set of agreed upon skills and systems, and it will be GREAT.  BUT,
>we could also create a great UNIVERSAL MODULAR GAME that could handle
>anyone's attribute/skill wishes if we really worked on it.

Murphy's Law corollary:
        You can please all of the people some of the time, or some of the
people all of the time.
        You cannot do both.

I don't want to sound too cynical, but what with all the well-thought-out ideas
floating about the list now regarding this one topic, I for one think it's time
to start consolidating, bearing in mind that as a group effort, compromises
will be necessary.  Kudos to all those who've contributed their ideas, and
let's keep this thing going!
